Hi,

I'm extremely new here. Although I'm actually a bit shocked it took  
me as long to find NEAT as it did, as it's the kind of thing I've  
been quite interested in for years.

Rather, it took until I came to write a proposal for an honours year  
project, when a potential supervisor pointed me towards NEAT after I  
spent a few minutes ranting at them about the kind of things I was  
interested in.

Anyway, now I'm hopefully going to be able to spend my year doing  
NEAT related things.

At the moment, I've yet to get the original NEAT package to  
compile... Because I'm trying to do so under OS X... Since while it  
would be possible to use Linux all year, I'd *vastly* prefer to sit  
in front of a mac.

So far, I think I've got everything I need via fink and I've changed  
paths in the Makefile appropriately, but just compilation of  
networks.cpp throws the to-be-expected screens and screens of errors...

Searching the list archive suggests I'm out of luck as far as finding  
an empathetic ear is concerned, but I just thought before I spend  
hours trying to get this thing to work, I'd see if anyone else has  
had any luck? =)

Thanks,

--
  Adam Wright  <zeno@...>
